title: Haagse Poort
text: The Haagse Poort () is an office building in <a href="The%20Hague">The Hague</a>, <a href="Netherlands">Netherlands</a>. It is an unusual, asymmetrical structure of 275 meters (or 900 feet) long that spans the Utrechtsebaan with a large arch. The Haagse Poort consists of a high-rise part and a low-rise part that are connected by the arch from the eighth floor. The tallest part amounts 70 meters (or 230 feet) and 17 floors. The building offers approximately 108,000 m² (or 1,160,000 sq ft) of office space.
